                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus> scrawls, illegible
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#70v" facs="075">Fol. 70v</locus> The middle line of the psalms is indented from the fore edge margin. In addition, a symbol of a cross in a later hand marks the midpoint of the Psalter
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#110r #110v #111r #111v #112r #112v #113r #113v #114r #114v #115r #115v #116r #116v 117r" facs="114 115 116 117 118 119 120 121">Fols. 110r, 110v, 111r, 111v, 112r, 112v, 113r, 113v, 114r, 114v, 115r, 115v, 116r, 116v, </locus>
                      <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual</span></ref>, added in a later hand
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      Numbered quires: quires 2–15
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#24v #51r #51v #56r #64v" facs="029 055 056 060 069">folss. 24v, 51r, 51v, 56r, 64v, </locus>, etc.);
                      and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#89r #123r #128r #132v" facs="093 127 132 137">89r, 123r, 128r, 132v, </locus>);
                      and in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#138r" facs="142"> f. 138r, line 7</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#125v" facs="130">125v, </locus>); text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#10r #25v #30r" facs="014 030 034">10r, 25v, 30r</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e6">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection
                      of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe reduces the font size
                      at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout). This scribe also will complete the line of text above or below the end of the line
                      (e.g., <locus target="#7v #73r" facs="012 077">fols. 7v, 73r</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>


                    </list>
